{"doc_urls":["ch01-00-getting-started.html#getting-started","ch01-01-installation.html#installation","ch01-01-installation.html#pre-compiled-binaries","ch01-01-installation.html#build-from-source-using-rust","ch01-01-installation.html#installing-the-latest-master-version","chapter_1.html#chapter-1"],"index":{"documentStore":{"docInfo":{"0":{"body":0,"breadcrumbs":4,"title":2},"1":{"body":11,"breadcrumbs":4,"title":1},"2":{"body":28,"breadcrumbs":6,"title":3},"3":{"body":45,"breadcrumbs":7,"title":4},"4":{"body":45,"breadcrumbs":7,"title":4},"5":{"body":0,"breadcrumbs":4,"title":2}},"docs":{"0":{"body":"","breadcrumbs":"Getting Started » Getting Started","id":"0","title":"Getting Started"},"1":{"body":"There are multiple ways to install dialect. Choose any one of the methods below that best suit your needs.","breadcrumbs":"Getting Started » Installation » Installation","id":"1","title":"Installation"},"2":{"body":"Executable binaries are available for download on the GitHub Releases page . Download the binary for your platform (Windows, macOS, or Linux) and extract the archive. The archive contains an executable which you can run to build your books. To make it easier to run, put the path to the binary into your PATH.","breadcrumbs":"Getting Started » Installation » Pre-compiled binaries","id":"2","title":"Pre-compiled binaries"},"3":{"body":"To build the dialect executable from source, you will first need to install Rust and Cargo. Follow the instructions on the Rust installation page . dialect currently requires at least Rust version 1.59. Once you have installed Rust, the following command can be used to build and install dialect: cargo install dialect-rs This will automatically download dialect from crates.io , build it, and install it in Cargo's global binary directory (~/.cargo/bin/ by default).","breadcrumbs":"Getting Started » Installation » Build from source using Rust","id":"3","title":"Build from source using Rust"},"4":{"body":"The version published to crates.io will ever so slightly be behind the version hosted on GitHub. If you need the latest version you can build the git version of dialect yourself. Cargo makes this super easy ! cargo install --git https://github.com/dialect-rs/dialect dialect-rs Again, make sure to add the Cargo bin directory to your PATH. If you are interested in making modifications to the software, check out the Contributing Guide for more information.","breadcrumbs":"Getting Started » Installation » Installing the latest master version","id":"4","title":"Installing the latest master version"},"5":{"body":"","breadcrumbs":"Chapter 1 » Chapter 1","id":"5","title":"Chapter 1"}},"length":6,"save":true},"fields":["title","body","breadcrumbs"],"index":{"body":{"root":{"1":{".":{"5":{"9":{"df":1,"docs":{"3":{"tf":1.0}}},"df":0,"docs":{}},"df":0,"docs":{}},"df":1,"docs":{"5":{"tf":1.0}}},"a":{"d":{"d":{"df":1,"docs":{"4":{"tf":1.0}}},"df":0,"docs":{}},"df":0,"docs":{},"g":{"a":{"df":0,"docs":{},"i":{"df":0,"docs":{},"n":{"df":1,"docs":{"4":{"tf":1.0}}}}},"df":0,"docs":{}},"r":{"c":{"df":0,"docs":{},"h":{"df":0,"docs":{},"i":{"df":0,"docs":{},"v":{"df":1,"docs":{"2":{"tf":1.4142135623730951}}}}}},"df":0,"docs":{}},"u":{"df":0,"docs":{},"t":{"df":0,"docs":{},"o":{"df":0,"docs":{},"m":{"a":{"df":0,"docs":{},"t":{"df":1,"docs":{"3":{"tf":1.0}}}},"df":0,"docs":{}}}}},"v":{"a":{"df":0,"docs":{},"i":{"df":0,"docs":{},"l":{"df":1,"docs":{"2":{"tf":1.0}}}}},"df":0,"docs":{}}},"b":{"df":0,"docs":{},"e":{"df":0,"docs":{},"h":{"df":0,"docs":{},"i":{"df":0,"docs":{},"n":{"d":{"df":1,"docs":{"4":{"tf":1.0}}},"df":0,"docs":{}}}},"l":{"df":0,"docs":{},"o":{"df":0,"docs":{},"w":{"df":1,"docs":{"1":{"tf":1.0}}}}},"s":{"df":0,"docs":{},"t":{"df":1,"docs":{"1":{"tf":1.0}}}}},"i":{"df":0,"docs":{},"n":{"a":{"df":0,"docs":{},"r":{"df":0,"docs":{},"i":{"df":2,"docs":{"2":{"tf":2.0},"3":{"tf":1.0}}}}},"df":1,"docs":{"4":{"tf":1.0}}}},"o":{"df":0,"docs":{},"o":{"df":0,"docs":{},"k":{"df":1,"docs":{"2":{"tf":1.0}}}}},"u":{"